  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of shelter rehabilitation and winterization assistance for the most vulnerable households in NW Syria 2020/2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">**Mercy-USA for Aid and Development in this project will support internally displaced persons (IDPs) in two components:
1-Rehabilitation/Upgrading of unfinished buildings in Idleb city to accommodate 200 HH,  1000 individuals (Men 200- Women 220- Boys 270- Girls 310) and ensure accessibility for people with disabilities in all buildings, privacy and safety for all vulnerable groups and link rehabilitation/Upgrade with free rental for IDPs for 6-12 months.

2-Winterization support in the form of in-kind, eco-friendly biofuel, and stove kits for IDPs living in informal tented settlements in Harbanush camps cluster -Ma&apos;arrat Tamasrin Sub-district &#x2013; Idleb governorate in addition to shelter rehabilitation beneficiaries in Idleb city
Total number of beneficiaries who will be targeted 4529 HH - 22645 individuals (Men 4529- Women 4982- Boys 6114- Girls 7020) by using in-kind modality for implementation as blanket distribution in the targeted IDP sites to all beneficiaries. 
Mercy-USA will target each household with in-kind 900 kg of olive pit fuel (300 kg per month) throughout the winter months (November 2020, December 2020 and January 2021). The initial fuel distribution will occur along with the stoves&#x2019; distribution or shortly after distributing the stoves to 100% of the targeted new IDPs who have arrived in the region after the escalation of violence in south Idleb. Mercy-USA will distribute olive-pit fuel to the beneficiaries directly on monthly allotments based on monthly distribution plan by specifying dates for each location. 

**Accountability to Affected population (AAP) will be given high priority in this project by communications and sharing information with beneficiaries during all project phases, as well as using complaints and feedback mechanism which is accessible to all beneficiaries especially the most vulnerable such as persons with disabilities, the elderly, women and girls, thus taking corrective actions based on need.
**HLP documents will be given high attention, so all HLP documents for all selected shelters should be available to be cleared. 
** Furthermore, MEAL plan will be for all project stages such as verification of vulnerability assessment, distribution monitoring, PDM, with using different MEAL tools.
**Reporting will be on timely basis according to the priority, ex., narrative report will be interim and final, while other reports will be on a weekly basis.</narrative>
  </description>
